[?2004l[?2004h> # Numpy 2.0 Compatibility Changes for pyknotid 0.5.3
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Summary
[?2004l[?2004h> Successfully compiled and installed pyknotid from source with Numpy 2.3.0 compatibility.
[?2004l[?2004h> All Cython extensions (chelpers, ccomplexity, cinvariants) are working correctly.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Changes Made
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ### 1. Python 3.13 Compatibility
[?2004l[?2004h> **File: pyknotid/make/torus.py**
[?2004l[?2004h> - Changed: `from fractions import gcd` → `from math import gcd`
[?2004l[?2004h> - Reason: In Python 3.9+, gcd was moved from fractions to math module
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ### 2. Numpy 2.0 Type Compatibility
[?2004l[?2004h> Replaced deprecated numpy type aliases with their explicit equivalents:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> **Files affected:**
[?2004l[?2004h> - pyknotid/spacecurves/spacecurve.py
[?2004l[?2004h> - pyknotid/make/periodic_knot.py
[?2004l[?2004h> - pyknotid/spacecurves/knot.py
[?2004l[?2004h> - pyknotid/spacecurves/openknot.py
[?2004l[?2004h> - pyknotid/representations/dtnotation.py
[?2004l[?2004h> - pyknotid/representations/representation.py
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> **Changes:**
[?2004l[?2004h> - `n.float` → `n.float64`
[?2004l[?2004h> - `n.int` → `n.int64`
[?2004l[?2004h> - `n.complex` → `n.complex128` (for dtype)
[?2004l[?2004h> - `isinstance(x, n.complex)` → `isinstance(x, (complex, n.complexfloating))`
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> **File: pyknotid/invariants.py**
[?2004l[?2004h> - Line 137: Updated dtype assignment to use n.complex128 and proper isinstance check
[?2004l[?2004h> - Line 177: Updated isinstance check for complex types
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Installation Steps Performed
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. Cloned pyknotid v0.5.3 from GitHub
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. Installed build dependencies (setuptools, cython)
[?2004l[?2004h> 3. Applied Numpy 2.0 compatibility fixes
[?2004l[?2004h> 4. Built Cython extensions using `python3 setup.py build_ext --inplace`
[?2004l[?2004h> 5. Installed to global Python environment using `python3 setup.py install`
[?2004l[?2004h> 
